articles.contents:
About Me
My name is Hannah, and I am a student at Williams
College. I love to cook and spend time outdoors.
About the Project
The title of my project is Fuel efficiency and weight. It is
a plot about cars and their mileage per gallon. This project was
completed as part of Kane’s data science bootcamp.
Goals
In my project, I might like to explore abortion access and its
importance.
Since the SCOTUS reversal of Roe v. Wade was so recent, it may be
difficult to find accurate data.

I also might like to explore environmental justice issues. Perhaps I
would look into health outcomes in neighborhoods near Superfund
sites.
“This is data science”

Preceptor Kane’s Free High
School Data Science Bootcamp
